race.description: In The Mounting Yard With Hugo Bladel 21/11 Hcp
race.comment: Tough. IT'S JAGGER TIME (1) performed above expectations here over 1100m beaten 1L. He's proven second-up and stepping up to 1400m suits. Maps well and has plenty up his sleeve. ANTHEIA (5) resumed in stronger at Hobart with a solid enough effort and then missed here by 1.5L over shorter when she proved difficult to load. Has her first crack at this distance and keeps the handy 2kg. Lightly raced and will get every chance to run it out. SIR JAG (11) has a wide gate to contend with but was tracking well before getting too far back here last time dropping to a short sprint. This suits better and with average luck he can feature. SAY IT WITH WORDS (7) hasn't been far away on the synthetic and jumps today from a low barrier. He's in the mix.
